burlap.domain.singleagent.tabularized

Class TabulatedDomainWrapper

  • java.lang.Object
    • burlap.domain.singleagent.tabularized.TabulatedDomainWrapper
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    DomainGenerator

    public class TabulatedDomainWrapper
extends java.lang.Object
implements DomainGenerator
    In general, it is suggested algorithms be designed to work with either factored state representations or the BURLAP State Hashing. However, some algorithms may be limited to working with states that have explicit enumerated values and with an entire state space already defined. In particular, if you are interfacing with code external to BURLAP this may be required. This domain generator can take any input domain and turns it into a domain in which states are represented by a single int attribute and are fully enumerated. The state space used must be enumerated before calling the generateDomain() method and is performed using a BURLAP state enumerator. In particular, seed states must be passed to this object and it will find all reachable states from the seed state and enumerate them.
    Author:
    James MacGlashan
